title: Rubio clashes with Democrats over decision to admit white South Africans
description: Tim Kaine condemns secretary of state for admitting Afrikaners while cancelling refugee schemes for othersMarco Rubio, the secretary of state, has defended the Trump administration’s controversial decision to admit 59 Afrikaners from South Africa as refugees after Tim Kaine, a Democratic senator from Virginia, claimed they were getting preferential treatment because they were white.Kaine, Hillary Clinton’s former running mate, challenged Rubio to justify prioritising the Afrikaners while cancelling long-standing refugee programmes for other groups that have been more documented as victims of conflict or persecution. title: Mother of jailed British-Egyptian activist resumes full hunger strike
description: Laila Soueif announces life-endangering action in protest over continued detention of Alaa Abd el-Fattah in CairoThe mother of the imprisoned British-Egyptian human rights activist Alaa Abd el-Fattah has announced she has resumed a near-total hunger strike, stopping taking the 300-calorie supplements she had been consuming on her partial hunger strike for the past three months.Since the start of her hunger strike 233 days ago, Laila Soueif, 69, has lost 36kg, about 42% of her original body weight, and now weighs 49kg. She is taking the life-endangering step in protest at the continued detention of her son in Cairo beyond his five-year sentence. Continue reading...
author: Patrick Wintour Diplomatic editor

title: Who is Darryl Nirenberg? Trump picks next US ambassador to Romania
description: Donald Trump has nominated Darryl Nirenberg, a Senate staffer with 40 years of foreign policy experience, as the next US Ambassador to Romania. Nirenberg's responsibilities will include strengthening ties, supporting military partnerships, and promoting American economic and security interests. He previously served as Counsel to the Senate Foreign Relations Committee and is currently a partner at Steptoe law firm.
author: TOI World Desk

title: US court says Trump administration may have violated order by sending migrants to South Sudan
description: Judge Brian Murphy accused the Trump administration of potentially criminal contempt for deporting migrants to South Sudan, violating a court order. The order was in place to protect migrants from being deported to countries where they might face torture or persecution without due process.
author: TOI World Desk
